CPEPrefix: cpe:/a:google:sentencepiece

Description:
SentencePiece is an unsupervised text tokenizer and detokenizer mainly for
Neural Network-based text generation systems where the vocabulary size is
predetermined prior to the neural model training. SentencePiece implements
subword units (e.g., byte-pair-encoding (BPE) [Sennrich et al.] and unigram
language model [Kudo.]) with the extension of direct training from raw
sentences. SentencePiece allows us to make a purely end-to-end system that does
not depend on language-specific pre/postprocessing.

Making new patches:
1. git commit changes, be sure to write a helpful commit message
2. Run `git format-patch -o third_party/sentencepiece/patches/ origin/main third_party/sentencepiece/src/`

Patches:
* 0001-Fix-absl-includes.patch - Rewrites absl includes from third_party/absl to
just absl.
* 0002-Remove-unused-absl-flags.patch - Removes some usage of absl flags which was not
needed for chromium.
* 0003-Update-absl-logging.patch - Prefixes logging statements with ABSL_ to
avoid conflict with Chrome logging.
* 0004-Disable-exceptions-in-darts.h-under-DARTS_DISABLE_EX.patch - Disables standard exceptions in darts.h under DARTS_DISABLE_EXCEPTIONS.
* 0005-Resolve-macro-collision-with-MediaPipe-s-RET_CHECK.patch - Resolves macro collision with MediaPipe's RET_CHECK macro by wrapping the RET_CHECK status return in parentheses.
* 0006-Remove-internal-absl-base-internal-endian.h-dependen.patch - Removes usage of internal absl headers for endianness and swaps it with standard C++ bit/endian.
* 0007-Remove-deprecated-attributes-to-fix-Werror.patch - Removes [[deprecated(...)]] attributes from sentencepiece_processor.h to prevent build failures under -Werror=-Wdeprecated-declarations.

In addition the unused data, python, third_party/absl, and
third_party/protobuf-lite directories were removed.

Rolling:
* Run roll.sh /tmp/sentencepiece to roll to head.
* If patching fails, you may need to update the patch files.
* Test changes by attempting to build it.
